依据《宪法》第12条第7项
Article 12, Section 7 of the Constitution,

57
00:03:06,010 --> 00:03:09,600
若被告招供是因受到刑讯 殴打 威胁 不正当的长期拘留
"If the defendant's confession was due to torture, assault, threat,

58
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,810
或遭遇欺瞒等审讯手段
prolonged imprisonment, or deception, etc.,

59
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:14,520
而非自行供述
and it seemed as though it wasn't a willful confession,

60
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:16,810
招供内容则不能作为 证明被告有罪的证据
it cannot be used to prove his guilt nor can it be used to penalize him."

61
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,020
也不能因此处罚被告
it cannot be used to prove his guilt nor can it be used to penalize him."

62
00:03:19,110 --> 00:03:22,280
你认为调查过程中可能存在 刑讯或殴打行为吗
Are you suggesting the possibility of torture or assault?

63
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:25,910
难到检方认为嫌疑人只有受到 刑讯或殴打才会进行虚假供述吗
Do you think one makes false confessions only because of torture or assault?

64
00:03:26,490 --> 00:03:29,530
检方在调查过程中有没有以 若自首就能够得到从宽处理这样的话
Didn't you placate the defendant by promising him that if he confesses,

65
00:03:29,620 --> 00:03:31,700
来劝诱被告呢
he'll be given some leniency?

66
00:03:32,450 --> 00:03:34,370
你也得想想你的家人啊
Think of your family.

67
00:03:35,540 --> 00:03:37,210
你有老婆和女儿啊
It says you have a daughter and a wife.

68
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:45,880
被告在案发当日 作为现行犯在现场被逮捕
The defendant was presumably caught in the act and arrested on the spot.

69
00:03:45,970 --> 00:03:50,310
紧接着被拘留了36天 并在此期间接受了调查
After that, he was questioned while being in custody for 36 days.

70
00:03:50,890 --> 00:03:52,680
他没有办法证明自己的清白
There was no way for him to prove his innocence,

71
00:03:52,810 --> 00:03:55,480
唯一能做的就是争取从宽处理
and the only thing he could do was ask for leniency.

72
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:57,480
如果在这样令人无措的情况下
Under these frustrating circumstances,

73
00:03:57,560 --> 00:04:00,570
被告受到了检方的劝诱呢
what if he was approached by the prosecutor with an offer?

74
00:04:01,070 --> 00:04:03,900
辩护人正将自己的推测 当作事实来陈述
The counsel is speaking as though his speculation is a fact.

75
00:04:03,990 --> 00:04:05,240
同意
Sustained.

76
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:07,070
辩护人 请注意
Take caution, counsel.

77
00:04:07,740 --> 00:04:08,700
好的
Yes.

78
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:15,040
各位陪审员
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

79
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:17,870
检方马上就要对被告进行询问
the prosecutors will soon question the defendant.

80
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:21,090
到时 大家需要注意的地方
What you must carefully watch for…

81
00:04:22,340 --> 00:04:27,260
不是被告看起来是否像要偷钱包的人
isn't whether the defendant seems like a person who might steal a wallet.

82
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:32,890
而是被告是否 是在准备偷钱包时被抓住的
You must carefully watch to see if the defendant really did get caught

83
00:04:33,470 --> 00:04:35,270
请大家注意这一点 我方陈述完毕
stealing the wallet. Thank you.

84
00:04:36,230 --> 00:04:38,020
检方 请进行询问
Prosecution, you may proceed.

85
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,400
被告
Defendant.

86
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:45,530
到现在为止 你总共拖欠了1300万韩元的医药费
You have a total of 13 million won of outstanding hospital bills.

87
00:04:45,610 --> 00:04:48,740
你在出狱后两个月的时间里 攒了多少钱
So, how much did you save for two months after you got out of prison?

88
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:54,660
你作为一名父亲 是否做到了全力以赴呢
Did you do your best as a father?

89
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,250
你没有尽到作为父亲的责任 不是吗
Weren't you neglecting your duty as a father?

90
