该提问与本次的案件无直接关联
The question is unrelated to this case.

92
00:05:07,420 --> 00:05:10,470
难道是因为被告是一名无能的父亲 所以才接受审判吗
Is the defendant in trial for being an incapable father?

93
00:05:11,050 --> 00:05:12,350
正如辩护人所言
As the counsel said,

94
00:05:12,430 --> 00:05:15,810
本案件的局限在于 只能够通过间接证据来进行判断
this case is limited to being judged by circumstantial evidence.

95
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:20,600
正因如此 我们必须要考虑被告所处的状况
Because of that, we must consider the situation the defendant was in,

96
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:24,820
因为做出某些行动的理由 或动机就在其中
as we can know the reason or motive behind the action.

97
00:05:26,190 --> 00:05:28,320
驳回辩护人提出的异议
The counsel's objection is overruled.

98
00:05:34,370 --> 00:05:35,660
《平价正义》
ONE DOLLAR LAWYER

99
00:05:35,790 --> 00:05:38,000
辩护人 请进行反询问
Counsel, you may cross-examine him.

100
00:05:38,710 --> 00:05:41,710
被告 你有四次盗窃前科吧
Defendant, you have been convicted four times for theft, haven't you?

101
00:05:42,330 --> 00:05:44,540
-对 -那你以前主要在哪里
-Yes. -Then, when you pickpocketed in the past,

102
00:05:44,630 --> 00:05:46,210
进行盗窃？
where did you usually do it?

103
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,630
千律师
Mr. Cheon.

104
00:05:50,130 --> 00:05:52,590
这应该是检察官才会问的吧
Isn't that a question the prosecutor should ask?

105
00:05:52,680 --> 00:05:53,930
被告 请回答
Please answer, defendant.

106
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:59,640
百货商场 酒店的桑拿房 银行
Department stores, hotel saunas, banks…

107
00:05:59,730 --> 00:06:00,850
主要在这些地方
Places like that.

108
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:03,360
-你为什么在这些地方进行盗窃 -因为可以偷到不少钱
-What was the reason? -Because I made good money.

109
00:06:03,440 --> 00:06:04,940
-可以偷到不少钱？-对
-You made good money? -Yes.

110
00:06:06,570 --> 00:06:09,900
所以说比起地铁或首尔站的洗手间
So, rather than subway stations or the restrooms at Seoul Station,

111
00:06:09,990 --> 00:06:13,740
你主要在酒店 百货商场 这些可以偷到不少钱的地方进行盗窃
you preferred department stores or hotels where you could make good money.

112
00:06:13,820 --> 00:06:17,620
那么以前你进行盗窃时
Then, when you pickpocketed in the past,

113
00:06:17,950 --> 00:06:20,660
被当场逮到过吗
did you ever get caught in the act?

114
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:23,080
-没有 -为什么呢
-No. -Why is that?

115
00:06:23,670 --> 00:06:25,250
那个…
Well…

116
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:27,710
被告 你以前进行盗窃时的 绰号是什么
Defendant, what was your nickname when you pickpocketed?

117
00:06:30,630 --> 00:06:32,050
被告 请回答
Please answer.

118
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:37,310
无影手
It was "Invisible Hand."

119
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:41,810
无影手？
Invisible Hand?

120
00:06:41,890 --> 00:06:43,650
各位 被告的绰号 并不是《无形的爱》
It isn't "Invisible Love," everyone.

121
00:06:44,230 --> 00:06:45,940
因为他盗窃时的速度很快
It was because he was so fast.

122
00:06:46,020 --> 00:06:48,320
他的手速很快 所以其他人根本看不到
His hand was so fast that you couldn't see it move.

123
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:52,030
他可是无影手啊 怎么可能会被抓到呢
So, how could he get caught when he's the Invisible Hand?

124
00:06:52,530 --> 00:06:55,870
被称作无影手的被告
Could the defendant who was called Invisible Hand

125
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,910
-偷取喝醉了的证人的… -审判长
-drunkenly steal the witness'-- -Your Honor.

126
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:02,710
案发当时 被告的右手受伤
During this incident, the defendant was caught using his left hand

127
00:07:02,790 --> 00:07:04,750
在他用左手试图进行盗窃时被抓住了
as he had injured his right hand.

128
00:07:04,830 --> 00:07:08,340
对 正是如此 案发当时被告右手处于受伤状态
Yes, that's right. During the incident, the defendant did injure his right hand.

129
00:07:08,420 --> 00:07:11,420
被告 你的右手为什么受伤了
Defendant, how did you injure your right hand?

130
00:07:16,050 --> 00:07:17,430
请回答
Please answer.

131
00:07:18,850 --> 00:07:20,220
这次出狱之后…
After I got out this time…

132
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,310
爸爸你能来 我真的特别开心
I'm so happy you're here.

133
00:07:23,020 --> 00:07:24,350
我本来想要金盆洗手
I was going to clean up my act.

134
00:07:24,440 --> 00:07:25,770
爸爸对不起你 昭弥
I'm sorry, Somi.

135
00:07:26,730 --> 00:07:28,440
但没有一个人相信我
No one believed me, though.

136
00:07:28,520 --> 00:07:32,240
今年的生日 你陪我一起过吧
Be here for my birthday this year.

137
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:33,320
拉钩
Promise.

138
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,120
所以我就用石头砸了我的右手
That's why I crushed my hand with a rock.

139
00:07:40,330 --> 00:07:41,500
我方有异议
Objection.

140
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:45,370
被告陈述的真实性 无法在法庭中得到确认
It's a testimony that cannot be proven in court.

141
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,630
被告的手也可能是在干活时受伤了
He could have hurt his hand while he was working.

142
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:50,000
同意
Sustained.

143
00:07:50,170 --> 00:07:51,090
同意什么
JIHUN:Sustain what?

144
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:54,880
我没有偷窃 你同意什么
I didn't do it, so what are you sustaining?

145
00:07:55,220 --> 00:07:56,300
被告
Defendant.

146
00:07:56,640 --> 00:07:58,550
你从刚才开始就把我当作罪犯对待
You treat me like a criminal already,

147
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,810
那这场庭审到底有什么意义
so what's the point of having a trial?

148
00:08:00,890 --> 00:08:02,390
被告 请肃静
Order, defendant!

149
00:08:02,470 --> 00:08:04,060
真的不是我干的
I really didn't do it!

150
00:08:04,140 --> 00:08:05,690
如果你继续喧闹就责令你离开法庭
If you don't calm down, you'll be removed.

151
00:08:06,020 --> 00:08:08,520
你们知道我坐在这里的心情吗
Do you know how it feels to be sitting here?

152
00:08:08,610 --> 00:08:11,730
在你们这些优秀的人眼中 我不过就是个有前科的垃圾
To you high-and-mighty people, I'm nothing but a convicted piece of trash.

153
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:13,440
法警 请将他带离法庭
Bailiff, remove him from court.

154
00:08:17,910 --> 00:08:19,030
李明浩
Mr. Lee Myeongho,

155
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,580
记住我刚才
remember what I said

156
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:25,210
说过的话
earlier.

157
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:27,830
你不是跟我约定好了嘛
You promised me.

158
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,210
请一定要遵守那个约定
Keep that promise.

159
00:08:30,290 --> 00:08:34,170
我也会遵守约定 让你女儿见到你
I'll keep the promise I made to your daughter to meet you.

160
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:35,510
你到底要怎么做
How on earth will you do that?

161
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:39,640
坐下吧
Please sit.

162
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:46,520
审判长和各位陪审员 十分抱歉
Your Honor and people of the jury, I apologize.

163
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:50,150
被告的情绪有些激动 我代他向各位道歉
I apologize on my defendant's behalf for his outburst.

164
00:08:50,980 --> 00:08:54,110
审判长 我还要向证人 也就是本案唯一的目击者
Your Honor, I have one last question to the victim who happens to be

165
00:08:54,480 --> 00:08:56,030
问最后一个问题
the only witness.

166
00:08:56,780 --> 00:08:58,660
证人 请到证人席
Witness, please approach the stand.

167
00:09:00,530 --> 00:09:02,830
请你闭上你的眼睛
Please close your eyes.

168
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:04,540
我为什么要闭上眼睛
Why should I do that?

169
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:07,460
这是为了更准确更细致地了解一下
It is to more thoroughly understand the circumstances

170
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:09,080
案发当时的状况
surrounding the case once again.

171
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:13,340
好 现在大家就把这里当作
All right. Let's say that

172
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:16,300
案发当日的首尔站洗手间
this place is Seoul Station's restroom on the day of the incident.

173
00:09:17,010 --> 00:09:20,010
-洗手间里一个人都没有吧 -对
-Was the restroom completely empty? -Yes.

174
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:23,470
-只有证人自己在方便 -对
-You were urinating by yourself. -Yes.

175
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:25,770
但当时被告在你身后
But you claim that the defendant

176
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:28,770
-拿了你的钱包 对吧 -对
-grabbed your wallet from behind, right? -Yes.

177
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:32,110
当时你虽然已经喝醉了 但还是察觉到了异常
Even though you were drunk, you sensed something was wrong,

178
00:09:32,190 --> 00:09:33,650
所以抓住了被告
so you caught him.

179
00:09:33,820 --> 00:09:34,900
是的
Yes.

180
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:37,440
但是…
But…

181
00:09:39,530 --> 00:09:41,990
你现在为什么没有察觉到呢
why couldn't you feel it just now?

182
00:09:42,950 --> 00:09:44,450
证人 你今天…
You had…

183
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:47,200
午饭吃了河豚清汤啊
puffer fish stew for lunch today.

184
00:09:47,290 --> 00:09:50,460
我也很喜欢吃河豚清汤 确实很好吃
By the way, I like puffer fish stew too. It's very delicious.

185
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:52,880
被告 你可以回到座位上了
You may go back, defendant.

186
00:09:52,960 --> 00:09:55,170
这是你的钱包吧
This is your wallet, isn't it?

187
00:09:58,130 --> 00:09:59,340
你这是在干什么啊
What the heck are you doing?

188
00:09:59,420 --> 00:10:01,840
你怎么能在神圣的法庭上 做出如此举动
How can you do this in this sacred court of law?

189
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:03,930
我只是想要确认一下
I was checking something.

190
00:10:04,140 --> 00:10:05,470
确认什么
Checking what?

191
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,850
你是想确认一下 他偷东西有多么熟练吗
Were you checking to see if he was good at pickpocketing?

192
00:10:07,930 --> 00:10:10,440
对 正是这样
Yes, that is exactly right.

193
00:10:10,520 --> 00:10:14,610
我想要确认一下 被告偷东西有多熟练
I wanted to check how good the defendant was at pickpocketing,

194
00:10:14,730 --> 00:10:15,980
与此同时 我也想要确认一下
and at the same time,

195
00:10:16,070 --> 00:10:18,190
与此同时 我也想要确认一下
I wanted to check how you reacted when you weren't drunk as well.

196
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:21,570
证人在没有喝醉的状态下会作何反应
I wanted to check how you reacted when you weren't drunk as well.

197
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:24,320
审判长
Your Honor,

198
00:10:25,700 --> 00:10:29,120
辩护人正在歪曲本次案件的真相
the counsel is distorting the truth of this case.

199
00:10:29,200 --> 00:10:32,920
当人闭上眼睛时 其他感官会变得更加敏感
When someone closes their eyes, their other senses become more sensitive.

200
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,630
但就像大家刚才看到的一样
But as you just saw,

201
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:37,880
证人在没有喝醉 头脑清醒的状态下
despite being completely sober,

202
00:10:37,960 --> 00:10:41,880
并没有察觉到被告将自己的钱包偷走
the witness didn't feel the defendant stealing his wallet at all.

203
00:10:41,970 --> 00:10:43,220
但是案发当晚
That night,

204
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,890
证人在喝醉的状态下
the witness was drunk

205
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:48,100
在能听到各种噪音的洗手间内
and he was in a bathroom filled with various noises,

206
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:51,480
察觉到被告要偷取他的钱包 并且抓住了他
but he felt the defendant grab his wallet, so he caught him.

207
00:10:52,060 --> 00:10:53,190
你没事吧
Are you okay?

208
00:10:53,270 --> 00:10:54,150
各位
Everyone,

209
00:10:55,230 --> 00:10:57,400
被告有四次盗窃前科
the defendant is a four-time convict of thievery.

210
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:59,860
但这是他第一次盗窃未遂
But this is the first time

211
00:10:59,940 --> 00:11:02,610
作为现行犯被抓住
he was caught in the act like this.

212
00:11:02,700 --> 00:11:06,530
为什么会这样 为什么之前他从未被当场逮到过
Why is that? Why wasn't he ever caught in the act before?

213
00:11:07,990 --> 00:11:08,910
因为被告
It's because…

214
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:12,000
是小偷中的高手
he was truly an expert.

215
00:11:12,660 --> 00:11:14,960
被叫做无影手的被告
The man who's called the Invisible Hand

216
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:18,130
却在偷喝醉的证人钱包时被逮住？
was caught trying to pickpocket the drunk witness's wallet?

217
00:11:19,380 --> 00:11:23,220
如果被告真的打算偷证人的钱包
Well, if the defendant really wanted to steal the witness's wallet,

218
00:11:24,260 --> 00:11:26,590
喝醉的证人真的会发现吗
would he really have been caught by the drunk witness?

219
00:11:27,350 --> 00:11:30,140
我认为这就是我们在本次案件中
I think this is a reasonable doubt

220
00:11:30,390 --> 00:11:33,180
应该拥有的合理怀疑
that we must have towards this case.

221
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,520
我方提问完毕
I rest my case.

222
00:11:52,580 --> 00:11:54,040
首尔中央地方法院
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT COURT

223
00:11:55,040 --> 00:11:57,040
你为什么不看到最后
Why aren't you staying until the end?

224
00:11:57,630 --> 00:12:00,300
玛丽应该不想让我继续看下去
Mari wouldn't want me to watch.

225
00:12:02,710 --> 00:12:04,550
作为辩护人 竟然让被告在法庭上偷东西
I can't believe he made him pickpocket someone in court.

226
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:06,130
真是他的一贯作风啊
How typical of him.

227
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:07,840
你记得吧
You remember, don't you?

228
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,600
记得
Yes.

229
00:12:09,720 --> 00:12:13,020
他那么自以为是 我想应该没有人愿意招他进律所吧
He acted so proud. I guess no one wanted him.

230
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:16,230
你去查一下他在哪个律所工作
Find out where he's working.

231
00:12:16,310 --> 00:12:18,020
难道你想招他进我们律所吗
You don't want to recruit him, do you?

232
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:21,020
你觉得他是那种招之即来的人吗
Do you think he would join us if we asked him?

233
00:12:21,110 --> 00:12:22,150
那你为什么…
Then, why…

234
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,320
走吧
Let's go.

235
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,530
各位陪审员中肯定有人认为
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury, I'm sure there are some of you who wonder

236
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,280
本案件只不过是盗窃未遂而已 没必要对被告进行处罚
Ladies and gentlemen of the jury, I'm sure there are some of you who wonder

237
00:12:29,410 --> 00:12:32,370
本案件只不过是盗窃未遂而已 没必要对被告进行处罚
why we have to punish someone for just an attempted crime.

238
00:12:35,210 --> 00:12:37,210
但像被告这样的盗窃惯犯
But in cases of repeated theft like the defendant,

239
00:12:37,290 --> 00:12:40,540
法律明文规定不能因为犯罪未遂
the law has stipulated that one can't simply get off

240
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:42,210
就对其减轻刑量
because it was an attempted crime.

241
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:46,550
因为即使是犯罪未遂 犯罪的性质也没有因此减轻
That's because the nature of the crime isn't lessened because it was an attempt.

242
00:12:47,130 --> 00:12:50,930
被告已经在监狱被关押过四次 但仍旧没有完全改过自新
If the defendant hasn't been reformed after going to prison four times before,

243
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,020
再一次经受矫正系统的教育
it would be best for him

244
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:57,390
对被告来说是最有益的
to go through the correctional system again and come out as a reformed person.

245
00:13:01,940 --> 00:13:03,530
对于多次犯下盗窃罪
Therefore, the prosecution thinks

246
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:05,440
或盗窃未遂罪的犯人
that someone who repeatedly committed theft

247
00:13:05,530 --> 00:13:07,400
依据《特定犯罪加 重处罚等相关法律》
or has attempted it

248
00:13:07,610 --> 00:13:08,990
应处以无期徒刑
must be punished in accordance with

249
00:13:09,070 --> 00:13:11,030
或三年以上有期徒刑
Act on the Aggravated Punishment of Specific Crimes

250
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:13,790
因此检方在此
which states they must serve a life sentence or over three years,

251
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:16,750
请求对被告处以五年有期徒刑
so I'd like to demand the defendant to serve five years in prison.

252
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:22,670
审判长和各位陪审员
Your Honor, and ladies and gentlemen of the jury,

253
00:13:23,420 --> 00:13:27,130
法律要求检察官证明被告确实有罪
our law requires the prosecution to prove the defendant's guilt

254
00:13:27,220 --> 00:13:30,890
并且不能存在任何合理性怀疑
beyond any reasonable doubt.

255
00:13:31,470 --> 00:13:33,350
存在疑点时 利益归于被告
"When in doubt, rule in favor of the defendant."

256
00:13:33,930 --> 00:13:37,020
存在疑点时 要有利于被告
When it's doubtful, it should be beneficial towards the defendant.

257
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:41,350
因为这就是《刑事法》的原则
That's because it's the principle of Criminal Law.

258
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:45,900
为什么存在疑点时 要做出对被告有利的判决呢
Why should it be favorable to the defendant when in doubt?

259
00:13:46,610 --> 00:13:49,150
万一让罪犯成为漏网之鱼怎么办
What if we really let go of a guilty person?

260
00:13:49,240 --> 00:13:51,200
比起将被告释放
It would be a relief to lock the defendant up

261
00:13:51,280 --> 00:13:52,410
好像把他关到监狱更令人放心
It would be a relief to lock the defendant up

262
00:13:52,490 --> 00:13:54,870
好像把他关到监狱更令人放心
rather than set him free, right?

263
00:13:55,490 --> 00:13:57,080
谁让他做了令人怀疑的事呢
"Who told him to do something suspicious?"

264
00:13:57,580 --> 00:14:00,920
我一辈子都不会做令人怀疑的事 所以这与我无关
"I'll never do anything suspicious, so it has nothing to do with me."

265
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,580
不是的
No, no.

266
00:14:04,630 --> 00:14:05,920
并不是这样
That's not right.

267
00:14:06,550 --> 00:14:07,630
虽然利用法律
It is important

268
00:14:08,460 --> 00:14:11,300
处罚有罪之人很重要
for our law to punish someone who committed a crime.

269
00:14:14,470 --> 00:14:16,010
但让无罪之人
But it is more important…

270
00:14:18,640 --> 00:14:21,640
免受处罚更为重要
to not punish someone who didn't commit the crime.

271
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:25,150
宁可放过十个有罪的人
Even if we lose ten criminals, "we shouldn't wrongfully imprison

272
00:14:25,230 --> 00:14:28,230
也不让一个无辜的人获罪
even one person."

273
00:14:28,320 --> 00:14:30,570
大家肯定都听过这句话
I'm sure you've heard that before at least once.

274
00:14:30,650 --> 00:14:34,700
为了这样 哪怕存在细小的疑点
In order to do that, our law requires that if it is even remotely doubtful,

275
00:14:34,820 --> 00:14:37,580
法律也会做出对被告更有利的判断
it should judge favorably to the defendant.

276
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:41,410
存在疑点时 利益归于被告
"When in doubt, rule in favor of the defendant."

277
00:14:41,580 --> 00:14:45,040
这条原则会在某一天最重要的瞬间
That principle will one day protect

278
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:50,260
守护最珍贵的人
someone most dear to you at the most important moment.

279
00:14:50,380 --> 00:14:52,970
也就是我们自己
Meaning, our very selves.

280
00:14:55,050 --> 00:14:58,720
陪审员席

281
00:15:15,570 --> 00:15:17,160
本庭判决如下
They have reached a verdict.

282
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,160
手术室
OPERATING ROOM

283
00:15:18,240 --> 00:15:19,790
根据陪审员的评议结果
According to the jury,

284
00:15:20,660 --> 00:15:22,960
一致通过了…
the verdict that they reached unanimously…

285
00:15:23,040 --> 00:15:24,460
检察官席
PROSECUTION

286
00:15:24,540 --> 00:15:27,460
对依据《特定犯罪加重处罚法》 以盗窃嫌疑
…regarding Defendant Lee Myeongho who was charged with theft

287
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:29,880
被起诉的被告李明浩
under the Act on the Aggravated Punishment of Specific Crimes...

288
00:15:36,050 --> 00:15:37,720
宣告无罪
...he is found not guilty.

289
00:15:37,800 --> 00:15:40,010
太好了
Yes!

290
00:15:41,520 --> 00:15:44,600
证人有可能将搀扶自己的被告
The witness may have misunderstood the defendant's attempt

291
00:15:45,440 --> 00:15:49,570
误认为是要盗取自己的钱包
to help the witness who was stumbling as trying to steal his wallet,

292
00:15:49,650 --> 00:15:53,780
因此很难证明检方的指控
so the prosecutor's charges are difficult to prove

293
00:15:53,860 --> 00:15:56,780
排除了所有的合理性怀疑
beyond reasonable doubt.

294
00:15:57,450 --> 00:15:58,410
被告
Defendant.

295
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,080
不对 李明浩
No, Mr. Lee Myeongho.

296
00:16:02,660 --> 00:16:05,000
庭审结束后 检察官会依据程序
After the trial, the prosecution will take steps

297
00:16:05,580 --> 00:16:07,000
马上将你释放
to release you immediately.

298
00:16:09,750 --> 00:16:10,670
谢谢
Thank you.

299
00:16:11,250 --> 00:16:12,340
辛苦了
You've been through a lot.

300
00:16:22,270 --> 00:16:24,180
首尔中央地方法院
SEOUL CENTRAL DISTRICT COURT

301
00:16:24,270 --> 00:16:26,730
千律师 谢谢你
Thank you, Mr. Cheon.

302
00:16:27,730 --> 00:16:30,270
你不用太担心 他们想要上诉应该很困难
Don't worry too much. It'll be difficult for them to appeal.

303
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:33,480
你快去医院吧 昭弥的手术已经顺利结束了
You should hurry. I was told that Somi's surgery went well.

304
00:16:34,070 --> 00:16:36,740
真的吗 那我就先走了
Really? I'll get going.

305
00:16:36,950 --> 00:16:38,610
谢谢
Thank you. Thank you.

306
00:16:42,660 --> 00:16:43,660
谢谢
Thank you.

307
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,880
恭喜你 千智勋律师
Congratulations, Mr. Cheon Jihun.

308
00:16:49,420 --> 00:16:52,340
有什么好祝贺的 这是值得祝贺的事情吗
What are you congratulating me for? Is this something to be congratulated?

309
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:55,300
这倒也是
You're right.

310
00:16:55,380 --> 00:16:56,470
我们握手吧
Let's shake hands!

311
00:17:00,850 --> 00:17:02,390
-好的 -白检察官
-Okay. -Ms. Baek.

312
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:03,850
你要上诉吗
Are you going to appeal?

313
00:17:03,930 --> 00:17:06,890
如果你不打算上诉的话 就快点进行生效判决吧
If you aren't, quickly give him the final ruling.

314
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,980
李明浩女儿昭弥的医药费 还急着要交 这你也清楚
You know that Mr. Lee's daughter, Somi, needs those medical bills.

315
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:13,440
就让他们得到刑事补偿金吧
Let's let them receive indemnification.

316
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:14,780
刑事补偿金？
Indemnification?

317
00:17:14,980 --> 00:17:17,280
对 一般是最低工资的五倍
Yes, it's usually five times the minimum wage.

318
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:19,660
事务长 今年的最低时薪是多少
Mr. Sa. How much is the minimum wage this year?

319
00:17:19,740 --> 00:17:21,530
-9160韩元 -那五倍是多少
-It's 9,160 won. -What is five times of that?

320
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:22,450
4万5800韩元
It's 45,800 won.

321
00:17:22,530 --> 00:17:25,660
-一天工作八小时呢 -36万6400韩元
-Since you work eight hours a day… -That's 366,400 won.

322
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:28,500
-那36天呢 -一千三百一十九万零四百韩元
-And 36 days of that? -It would be 13,190,400 won.

323
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:30,630
到现在为止 昭弥的医药费一共是多少
Lastly, how much is Somi's medical bills until now?

324
00:17:30,710 --> 00:17:35,090
1300万8128韩元
It's 13,008,128 won!

325
00:17:35,170 --> 00:17:36,920
这样一来 就能解决昭弥医药费的问题了
Then, her medical bills have been sorted out!

326
00:17:39,550 --> 00:17:42,180
-你们这是干什么啊 -不愧是白检察官
-What are you doing? -You're the best, Mr. Cheon!

327
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,600
因为感谢你才这样 真的十分感激你
It's because I'm so thankful to you

328
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:47,270
帮忙解决昭弥医药费的问题
for taking care of Somi's medical bills.

329
00:17:47,930 --> 00:17:49,770
我感觉有些饿了
I'm starting to get hungry.

330
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:51,440
你饿了吧 我们去吃什么
I know. What should we eat?

331
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:53,110
白检察官 你喜欢吃炸酱面吗
Do you like jjajangmyeon, Ms. Baek?

332
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:55,650
不 我不喜欢吃炸酱面
No, I don't like jjajangmyeon.

333
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,820
你不喜欢吃炸酱面啊
You don't like jjajangmyeon?

334
00:17:58,190 --> 00:18:00,200
-那… -那么
-Then… -Then,

335
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:03,530
一起去我家吃五花肉 怎么样
what about pork belly at my place? It's been a while.

336
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:04,950
你喜欢吃五花肉吗
